<br>
For instance, for mages they could have gone with AA Conjurer and Summoner.<br>
<br>
AA Conjurer might have included AA skills like:<br>
<br>
Reduced mana on summoned items.<br>
Reduced cast time on summoned items.<br>
Several new 'uber' summoned items:<br>
--pet weapon similar to the cleric hammer<br>
--Damage 14+ arrows.<br>
--Improved Armor summons.<br>
--New muzzle with higher haste<br>
--300+ range, high damage throwing weapons<br>
--Stat enhancing food and drink<br>
--Weapons Melee will actually want, stats similar to Centi weapons or better, 1 of each type:1hs, 2hs, 1hb, 2hb, pierce, and H2H, and all with possible vs. summoned bane damage, or Elemental damage, or both.<br>
--Focuses that improved their areas from 15-35%, instead of the current ones that go 1-20%.<br>
--Items with FT and Regen on them<br>
--Items with Permanant EB, Lev, Etc on them, instead of charges.<br>
<br>
Summoner AA Skills could include:<br>
--Pet Hold<br>
--Frenzied Burnout (one that works)<br>
--Pet mana reduction<br>
--Pet cast time reduction<br>
--Pet resist enhancement<br>
--Pet ATK upgrade<br>
--Pet Dmg upgrade<br>
--Pet AC upgrade, various other upgrades, you get the idea.<br>
--Reagentless COH<br>
--70min refresh summon someone outside the zone. (pop up a box, you type their name and *poof* there they are if they click yes)<br>
--DC summoned mobs only (ok, this has probably no use, but WTH)<br>
--Passive burnout skill:all pets summoned automaticaly have Burnout 3, unless the mage casts a better version.<br>
--15min refresh pet Complete Heal.  Usefull for emergencies and hard grouping, but not every fight.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
This way, a mage would have to choose enhanced pet skills, or enhanced summoned items, especially if the items summoned were actually usefull to the guild at large.  AA title would differ between what you chose, Master Summoner, or Master Conjurer..  You get the idea.<br>
